<br>
[quote]'I will study RabidSheep's posts in detail, and see if I can summarize them for others[/quote]<br>
<br>
Do that<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    I can give a (another) quick summarize too:P<br>
<br>
Make a 61 air pet, velocity, BO5, taunt off. Pet guard here, and go find a lonely larvae or undead vassal (those are the ones I have tested it with so far, but I do believe it is doable with others too).<br>
<br>
I pull with malosini. Try to get off a bolt before sending pet, its not nessesary, but it helps. then send the pet. run (with sow/soe) and blast. Normal aggro kiting. Only we dont have snare, we have stun. its not as good, but it gets the job done. The mob will turn on your air pet sometime, then you chain it. after that, it will go a little slower (unless you have suspend minion) but it works just fine. after a few minutes, the mob is dead.<br>
<br>
This takes a lot of mana, this is not easy like we had it before pop, but its FUN! its good exp (even compared to pop exp). Its NOT fun if you dont cannibalize pets for mana.. I use from 50 to 60 % mana per kill. about 2 min max downtime, max. most of my downtime comes from finding solo mobs, but after a while I know where the spawnplaces are. I hold about 5 or 6 spawnplaces cleared.<br>
<br>
I only use one pet, if nothing goes wrong.<br>
<br>
I dont really care if you belive me or not, but it annoys me to see everyone saying they cant solo when I (with middle/low gear for a 65 mag) and several other mages can solo just fine, just a completely different way then I used to solo.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227830">Rabids Arch Mage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rabidsheep>rabidsheep</A> at: 12/11/02 3:03:02 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 588<br> <font color=#333333>(12/12/02 7:43:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=416.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters the new uber pet class  </span><hr size=1> Agro kiting, mm. I have developed some tricks for it.<br>
<br>
A very cheesy tactic which I use frequently, but have always looked down on.<br>
<br>
It's all about getting as much agro as you can in the shortest amount of time.<br>
<br>
First of all, use the air pet, the water pet is a piece of crap.<br>
<br>
If the mob you want to agro kite has low resists, screw malosini. Stand at max range and fire off 2x firebolts, and whatever other nukes you can fit in. Then, if you still have time, throw down a malosini. You could also throw down the malosini when your pet stuns it.<br>
<br>
When the mob turns on your pet, blast it's head off with firebolt of tallon.<br>
<br>
If your pet is at low health, *and the mob is agro on you*, you may want to consider /pet holding it so that it regens to full hp. It regens 3% per tick. Unfortunately, the dumb air pet casts invis, otherwise this technique would work with a velocitied pet even if the mob was still agro on it. You should all really /feedback to have the invis removed from 61 air, it has no place but to annoy and force us to get DMF/SoE/Acument. Doesn't even help on PVP since everyone probably has see invis on those servers anyway.<br>
<br>
If your pet is low health and firebolt won't turn the mob, get some distance between you and the mob and start casting a new pet. Type /pet report health. Spam it up. If your pet has dodged a few attack rounds and is still at 30%, duck and recast. Be quick to resummon the new pet eventually though, don't push your pet's avoidance limit--don't keep recasting forever, la~ you're gonna have to chain a new pet eventually anyway, might as well do it before your pet ninjadies without enraging. Hopefully though, your pet will enrage, duck and recast as soon as you see this. Make the new pet. Since we don't have a 0.5 second casting burnout+ds spell, it will be unbuffed and take forever to kill the mob... BUT it will start fresh with zero agro. Obviously, use a suspend2'd pet if you have one, but don't summon it weapons or anything because that's a waste of downtime. Velocity is also broken on Suspend2'd pets. please /bug this.<br>
<br>
When your pet stuns, you can toss the mob a nuke. Scars of sigil is good for this. Other nukes like char might be good too, haven't tested yet because this part is of little consequence. Scars of sigil will not keep a mob off your pet forever, and is not enough to kill a mob unless you have a ton of mana. However, it speeds up the process and adds 450 more damage that your next pet has to do, if you decide to make another pet.<br>
<br>
Alternatively, you could just get a ton of range and cast a real nuke. I caution you on this, because you need a lot of room &amp; could run into adds, and some mobs, like ice burrowers, will just turn on your pet if you're too far away, then, in the cast of ice burrowers, kill your pet in 15 seconds and continue chasing  you. Also, the wurm things in PoV have nasty warping bugs, you wanna keep those confined to a small area preferably near their spawn point.<br>
<br>
If you have infinite room to kite and the mob won't agro your pet if you're out of a certain range, exploit bolts. Bolts don't do a range check until the spell is FINISHED casting. That means you could be well out of shock of fiery blades range(not counting that bolts have longer ranges) and start casting the bolt. As long as the mob is within 300 feet when the spell's casting time is over, the spell will cast.<br>
<br>
You will need to cannipet during downtime. <br>
<br>
You will need to use more than 1 pet against most dark blue to 65's.<br>
<br>
Normal charm is utterly unbalanced &amp; overpowered and probably needs to be nerfed, but although it involves 'pets' it is a completely different ability from our pets and should not be compared so directly.<br>
<br>
Dire charm is utterly unbalanced &amp; completely overpowered yet is completely risk free. It's also a very similar to not only our pets, but to rogues, monks, and rangers. Single weilding, hasted dire charm pets in the planes will do at least 90dps. This needs to be nerfed badly. Dire charmable mobs in the planes should be marginally better than animations when fully equipped &amp; buffed, at best.<br>
<br>
Group exp is better than solo exp.}<br>
<br>
Get over it. <p>Happy trails.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A> at: 12/12/02 7:45:29 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
